content: Motherhood is constant juggling. It is respecting your child for who they are...It is having no playbook because kids are just not robots.... It is the knowledge that you cannot do it all, you can only do your best. It is knowing priorities...It is trying the homemade recipe your kid makes, no matter how questionable...It is a serious loss of sleep, like, for YEARSüò≥üò≥...It is heartwarming and hilarious...It is both the greatest sacrifice and the greatest gift....It is teaching your kids the importance of strength and independence - and convincing yourself to let go of them a bit so they can learn to overcome life's struggles. It is by far the toughest yet most rewarding gig around. It is knowing the deepest meaning of love....So to every hard working, smart, and dedicated mommy.... I salute you. You may think no one notices... BUT.... make no mistake.. you are doing great work!!!!

content: Major props to our girlies tonight!! It has not been an easy 24 hours for our family... we were evacuated from our home all last night because our neighbor's home was on fire and the fear was, our home wasn't safe either. content: My heart is heavy this Memorial Day. Our team coverage, here. Awful. These are an elite parachute group of Navy SEALS known as Leap Frogs. 1 died when his parachute malfunctioned at Liberty State Park. The planned Fleet Week event continued even after it happened, leaving spectators so troubled and confused. Passengers on a nearby ferry, were told not to take pictures. It was only 2 days ago I watched yet another group of Army guys do similar stunts without a hitch..at the air show in Long Island. That was a happy day. But at today's Navy demonstration.... the unthinkable. Rest In Peace.  üá∫üá∏
name: Stacey Sager
title: U.S. Navy Seal killed in accident at Fleet Week event
